Old Fashioned Short Cake
  --Jennifer Kuchnicki Merzlicker

2 c ap flou
1 c sugar
4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp nutmeg (optional)
1/2 c cold butter, cubed
1/3 c milk
1 large egg

Preheat oven to 450F (320C). Grease an 8" baking pan (or muffin tin). Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, and nutmeg together in a large bowl. Cut in butter with a pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Beat together milk and egg in a small bowl; stir into flour mixture until batter is just blended. Spread batter in the prepared baking pan, or dole out equally to muffin tin. Bake until golden, ~15 min. Cool in the pan for 10 min before removing to cool completely on a wire rack.


Note: add vanilla

